~hah, remember that line from The Simpsons? Tcha dude!.. yeah, its 7:15 am, and I'm up, what the crap!  I cant sleep. ehh.  I think I fell asleep at 1:30am, cus thats the last time I went to the bathroom, and then I went to the bathroom at 6:30am, and I've been awake since, sigh.. I think its the damn 'energy drink' from last night that did me in, dammit, oh well.. I bet I'll totally crash and burn later this afternoon.  I listened to some good ol' U2, and Modest Mouse, and other good stuff on the radio last night at 1am, good times... cant believe I'm awake at this hour

I wish there was neon pink on this thing, oh well.  I feel like I am, yet again, in the middle of another mood swing, dammit.  Oh well.  Whatever.  I've been thinking lately, well, a little bit at least, and I think I've finally started to "really" grow up, I'm slowly.. slooooowly growing into my own skin, and it only took nearly 20 years, sigh, but hey, Gotta do it at some point, right?  I am slowly getting on the road to independence, and growing out of my childish ways.  No more useless giggling like a schoolgirl over boys, hah, we all remember last yrs situation right?  I miss my friends, I miss being with them, talking you them.  Funny how I refered to my friends as "them" and not "you guys", dontcha think.  I miss you Sam, take care of yourself.  I miss Megan too, hope she's doing well, love to see her again some day. I don't know... I miss boys too, heh.. hopefully once school starts in, like, 3 more weeks, I will not be quite as deprived, heh.  Finally moving on in life, yet again, time to go at it full steam ahead.  I really need a good pick me up.. a boost to my.. I dont know, self esteem? self image?  I sometimes feel underappreciated.. for all that I do??.. no biggie though, whatever-- see, I'm so laid back, I don't even really care,... whatev.. I don't know..

I need to do something with myself, to keep myself busy..

..going to coffee with a boy would be nice.. sigh..

Right now, I know I need to go to bed, and thats all I know...

~whatev, I'll be just fine soon, back to my usual self.. damn mood swings.. I think

~So, I've just gotten yet another email from HFS informing me that I've been offered yet another apt in Stevens Court.. which is really cool.. I just don't know what to do... From what I've calculated, the apt would cost just as much, if not less than the dorms, always a good thing, since I have no money.. from what I've calculated, the dorm, with a "basic" meal plan, will cost $2,042 per qtr. , while the apt costs $1,587/ rent for 3 months, of course, one has to add the cost of groceries/ household items, which I'm guessing would cost me about $150 per month ( Sarah says she spends about $130/ month, so I'm basing my own guess off of that), so with that, my grand total for the apt would cost $2,037.. yep a whopping $5 cheaper than the dorm, BUT keep in mind, food is much much cheaper when its not purchased in a (new remodeled, and therefore very expensive) dorm (prime example: the exorbitant food prices at McMahon 8), like, I can buy a box of cereal that'll feed me for, say, atleast 2 weeks, for $3, while at Terry, $3 will buy 3 single serving boxes of cereal-- 3 days worth of cereal, not 3 weeks-- or $1 will buy you one measly, lousy pint of milk, ripoff.. sigh.. also, I would assume that living in a 4 person apt, one would not have to deal with an entire floor of 50+ PMSing girls.. all at the same time, that would be pure.. hell... on.. earth.. And I'm guessing in an apt there would be less distracts, more time to focus on a double major-- less unfocused, idiot freshman to deal with... I sure as hell don't mind cleaning, cleaning is good for the soul, besides, we're all gonna have to do it eventually, we all have to grow up and live on our own and fend for ourselves eventually.. while.. cooking- not my forte.. but hey..thats what frozen chicken, ramen noodles, soups, various frozen delights, and microwaves are for! right!?! .. sigh.. well.. You Know You're From Washington When...
You know the state flower (Mildew) You feel guilty when you don't recycle. You use the phrase "sun break" and know what it means. You know more than 10 ways to order coffee. You know more people who own boats than air conditioners. You feel overdressed wearing a suit to a nice restaurant. You've stood on a deserted corner in the rain waiting for the "Walk" Signal. You understand that if it has no snow or has not erupted, it is not a real mountain. You can taste the difference between Starbuck's, Seattle's Best, Veneto's, Peet's, and Tully's. You know the difference between Chinook, Coho, and Sockeye salmon. You consider swimming an indoor sport. You are well versed in the difference between Japanese, Chinese and Thai food. In winter, you go to work in the dark and come home in the dark -- while only working eight-hour days. You never go camping without waterproof matches and a poncho. You are not fazed by "Today's forecast: showers followed by rain," and "Tomorrow's forecast: rain followed by showers." You have no concept of humidity without precipitation. You can point to at least two volcanoes, even if you cannot see through the cloud cover. You notice "the mountain is out" when it is a pretty day and you can actually see it. You put on your shorts when the temperature gets above 50, but still wear your hiking boots and parka. You switch to your sandals when it gets about 60, but keep the socks on. You've actually used your mountain bike on a mountain. You think people who use umbrellas are either wimps or tourists. You knew immediately that the view out of Frasier's window was fake. You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends from Washington.
